episodes.overview: Scarlett and Kirsty rub each other up the wrong way. Daniel and Zara keep it a secret that they are set on giving up their partnerships. Luca has a crush on Jamie. Bear encourages two members of the digital literacy group to work together.

episodes.name: Ostrich
episodes.overview: Scarlett and Kirsty have to deal with a computer engineer, while Daniel and Zara put their plans for the future to Bear. Al has to deal with a patient who seems to focus on everything except herself.

episodes.name: Elbows and Knickers
episodes.overview: Zara and Emmas night out takes more than one unexpected turn. Scarlett gets an offer that she has to consider, while Luca and Jamie go on a first date.

episodes.name: The Absence of Proof
episodes.overview: Rob decides to take the lead in Karens new exercise regime, Sid discovers Scarletts secret, and Daniel has difficult decisions to make when dealing with a family in crisis.

episodes.name: Where The Streets Know Your Name
episodes.overview: Karen returns to work and meets Kirsty, Scarletts day takes a turn for the worst, and Rob steps in when an arrest starts to look wrong.

episodes.name: Money and Other Problems
episodes.overview: Scarlett gets annoyed at everyone checking up on her, Ruhma confronts Kirsty, and Bear gets embroiled in a family feud.

episodes.name: Radio Frequency
episodes.overview: Rob manages to get Karen out and about, but all is not as it seems. Brian comes to a decision, but can he tell Scarlett? Emma gets an unexpected request while hosting her radio show.

episodes.name: Resistance
episodes.overview: Karens determination to stay calm and positive hits a snag in the form of Al. Scarlett struggles with Brians decision to leave.

episodes.name: Balance of Power
episodes.overview: Luca returns to face Jamie. Scarletts plans to get the better of her landlady nearly fall at the first hurdle. When a young man accuses a well-known businessman of sexual assault, Rob finds himself battling powerful forces, intent on scuppering his investigation.

episodes.name: Letting Go
episodes.overview: Karens new exercise regime causes a stir at the Mill, while Scarletts plan to do a runner is jeopardised by a call from the landlady. Fearing that her widowed mother is going off the rails, a woman turns to Jimmi for help  but what is really going on?

episodes.name: Say Sorry
episodes.overview: Scarlett discovers that some problems dont go away, but at least she has friends. Emma meets a brave mother who is struggling to escape her abusive husband.

episodes.name: Lost
episodes.overview: When Rich and Kirsty receive an unexpected visitor, Rich decides to have some fun. Luca is nervous about seeing Jamie again, and Ruhma is on hand at a community event for a miscarriage support group, where the young couple who have helped to organise it find themselves needing support.

episodes.name: The Leaving Party
episodes.overview: Daniel and Zara attend a very unusual party where they are caught up in the tensions between a patient, his new partner and his ex-wife.

episodes.name: Hell is Empty
episodes.overview: There are multiple casualties when an explosion rips through a medical conference, but what caused it and which of the Mill staff are caught up in the carnage?

episodes.name: Aftershock
episodes.overview: Zara deals with the aftermath of the explosion, while Daniel tries to get everyone to speak to a counsellor, with varying results. Rob and Jimmi help a police officer who was part of the rescue team in the explosion, but all is not what it seems.

episodes.name: Ways of Seeing
episodes.overview: Rob struggles to adjust to living with Scarlett, Emma challenges Luca to cook a meal, and Bear is caught between two old friends whose marriage is breaking down.

episodes.name: Nurses and Doctors
episodes.overview: Daniel and Zara throw Joe a birthday party. Ruhma and Scarlett are confused by Kirstys living arrangements with Rich. Sid and an agency nurse clash in a number of unexpected ways.

episodes.name: Hearts and Minds
episodes.overview: Kirsty and Rich come to an understanding, Rob treats Karen to a special night, and Emma encourages Luca to talk to Jamie. Ruhma goes on a blind date, meeting an interesting man, but is he all he appears to be?

episodes.name: Persuasion
episodes.overview: Ollie comes home from the army with a surprise, while Nina arrives at the Mill and makes her mark. Scarlett is asked out by a former work colleague, but he is being coached on how to seduce her.

episodes.name: The Unusual Suspects
episodes.overview: Nina wants to join the Mill as a partner, Kirsty and Rich have to tell Ollie the truth, and Al is recruited by a true crime podcaster to help solve a mystery.

episodes.name: Digging In
episodes.overview: Kirsty does her best to protect Ollie, but is it enough? Daniel and Zara learn more about Ninas plans, and Jimmi tries to help a promising young cricket star face up to her problem.

episodes.name: The Right Move
episodes.overview: Rob and Karens plans surprise everyone, Kirsty and Rich worry about Ollies future, and Zaras patient is determined to find her missing parent, but is all as it seems?

episodes.name: Runaway Train
episodes.overview: Rob and Karens plans surprise everyone, Kirsty and Rich worry about Ollies future, and Zaras patient is determined to find her missing parent, but is all as it seems?

episodes.name: Horse to Water
episodes.overview: A new doctor ruffles feathers on their first day at the Mill. Sid worries about a young boy and his older brother, and is Kirsty ready to face her new life?

episodes.name: As One Door Closes...A Window Opens
episodes.overview: Kirsty opens up to Karen. Luca and Jamies date night doesnt go as planned. Al worries about Connie, an elderly patient in an unlikely relationship.

episodes.name: Daddy Cool
episodes.overview: Ruhma tries to help some new dads, while Suni charms the team at The Mill.

episodes.name: Just Like Starting Over
episodes.overview: Luca meets Jamies mum, Nina has an idea to help The Mill, and Suni helps a student struggling to leave their old life behind.

episodes.name: Dafydd's Day Off
episodes.overview: Ruhma and Sid encounter an issue with the dads group. Luca helps Jamie buy a bed, but can he lie in it? Dafydd tries to celebrate St Davids Day, but Jimmi has to spoil the party.

episodes.name: Cal Patterson Saves the Day
episodes.overview: Sid fails to get through to Damien, Luca comes clean to Jamie, and Nina helps a patient whose carer is ill.

episodes.name: The Fallout
episodes.overview: Sid finds out the truth about Damien, Luca lashes out, and Scarletts first VPAS shift doesnt go to plan.

episodes.name: End of the Peer Show
episodes.overview: The staff at The Mill are less than excited about the peer review day. Can Nina make it work?

episodes.name: 5,000th
episodes.overview: Things are still frosty between the staff after the peer reviews, while Kirsty deals with Ollies unwelcome surprise. Ruhmas colleague delivers her 5,000th birth, but things dont go to plan.

episodes.name: An Old Friend
episodes.overview: Daniel gets exciting news from an old friend but discovers something unpleasant in the process.

episodes.name: The Box
episodes.overview: Karen discovers the wonders of talking texts, and Rich uses Ollie to spend time with Kirsty. Bear is roped into wearing an interesting costume to raise money for charity, but has to give chase in it when a thief makes off with the donation box.

episodes.name: Male Order
episodes.overview: Luca and Suni try to iron things out. Ollie tries to help his dad, but Rich has an unwanted request. Emma has to placate an irate mother when she finds out her daughter wants to have a baby.

episodes.name: Anything but Magnolia
episodes.overview: Daniel gets a worrying phone call, while Rob and Karen have something to celebrate. Rob has to deal with warring neighbours, and Karens quest for the perfect wallpaper gets her in trouble.

episodes.name: If Wishes Were Horses
episodes.overview: Rob and Karens big night out takes a shocking turn, and Scarletts evening ends in disaster. Jimmis advice falls on deaf ears.

episodes.name: Exit Trial
episodes.overview: Suni helps a troubled young footballer deal with a new challenge while going through some life-changing moments himself.

episodes.name: After You
episodes.overview: Two weeks have passed, and while everyone tries to process their grief, Imogen is worried about Rob, and Ollie finds himself stuck in the middle.

episodes.name: Homesick
episodes.overview: Ollie makes a decision, while Emma tries to get Rob to open up. Al meets a Chinese student who seems to be missing home, but what is really going on?

episodes.overview: Nina tries to stand up to Auntie Binita, while Rich has big news for Kirsty and Ollie. When a confused woman turns up at the Mill, with no memory of how she got there, Bear uncovers a tragic story.

episodes.name: Home Comforts
episodes.overview: Imogen worries about Rob in the aftermath of Karen, while Suni takes Bear and Sid to a restaurant opening. Jimmi counsels a mother and daughter who are dealing with trauma that goes back decades.

episodes.name: Optics
episodes.overview: Bear meets an old friend from university he used to have a crush on, and Jimmi discovers the Beechwalk is being sold. New midwife Malika struggles with a young couple who have just given birth but are clearly hiding deeper problems.

episodes.name: The Testing Place
episodes.overview: During Ramadan, two women are brought together by tragedy, but can the community help?

episodes.name: Ring-Fenced
episodes.overview: Kirsty upsets Ollie. Scarlett sets him straight. Meanwhile, Bear doesnt know what to do about Tanisha. When Luca helps Anna, whose husband doesnt like her learning English, he becomes worried that something more sinister is going on.

episodes.name: Special Interests
episodes.overview: Rich and Kirsty hide what happened from Ollie, and Suni charms Scarlett and Bear over lunch. Meanwhile, Daniel helps a mother who thinks her daughter might be autistic.

episodes.name: Point of View
episodes.overview: Imogen worries Rob is seriously unwell. Nina, Scarlett and Zara attend a council meeting about the Beechwalk. Emma helps a wheelchair user who is trying to get the council to fix potholes in the street, which are creating havoc for everyone.

episodes.name: An Audience with Al Haskey
episodes.overview: Imogen talks to Sid about Rob, Ollie and Scarlett continue to flirt, and Bear shows Tanisha the mill. Al is shocked to meet a patient who is live-streaming his life.

episodes.name: Land's End
episodes.overview: Zara plots with Al to save the Beechwalk, while Jimmi and Nina take on the council. Kirsty is delighted to have the upper hand at home. And Suni has some bad news for a man planning a charity cycle.

episodes.name: The Value of Nothing
episodes.overview:
Zara goes undercover  but has she made a terrible mistake? Bear is impressed by Tanishas lifestyle. Scarlett becomes Ninas latest recruit.

Malika tries to help when a private midwife has a tricky birth to deal with.

episodes.name: Winds of Change
episodes.overview: Rob and Imogen say an emotional farewell to Karen. How far will Zara go to save the Beechwalk? And Luca is surprised by his friend Coras big decision.

episodes.name: Duckling
episodes.overview: On a home visit, Al meets a mother struggling to face the outside world, and some shocking news pushes the already pressured family to the limit.

episodes.name: The Gift Horse
episodes.overview: Nina unveils her plan to save the Beechwalk, Al clashes with Kirsty, and Sid meets a taxi driver who is struggling to reconnect with his son.

episodes.name: Give Them What They Want
episodes.overview: Rob makes a big decision about the future. Will Nina be able to pull off her big plan? Tanisha makes a tempting offer, and Bear and Sid try to help a young man who fears his illness has returned.

episodes.name: Animals
episodes.overview: Its the day of the Beechwalk performance. Can Nina pull it all together? Eco protesters target the event, frustrating both the team and the audience.

episodes.name: Islands
episodes.overview: Bear receives an offer, the fate of The Beechwalk is decided, and Scarlett has an idea. A mum struggling to put food on the table lets pride get in the way of helping her son  with potentially fatal consequences.

episodes.name: Acting the Maggot
episodes.overview: Rob makes a step in moving on, Zara is excited about a job opportunity, and Luca turns to unusual methods to help a patient.

episodes.name: Lost Time
episodes.overview: Sid and Kirsty encounter a patient who is losing time.

episodes.name: Tender Sting
episodes.overview: Scarlett and Ollie struggle with their master plan, Nina is unsure about Bears replacement receptionist, and Daniel struggles to help a grieving friend.

episodes.name: Crash and Burn
episodes.overview: Rob cooks up a storm, Zara gets to grips with her new role, and Bear meets an old college friend with big ambitions.

episodes.name: Red
episodes.overview: Emma and Rob are mortified after their night of drinking, Zara enjoys her first day at Letherbridge University, and Al is curious about why Rosie has returned to the Mill.

episodes.name: The Cry
episodes.overview: Scarlett and Ollie have more fun pulling pranks as the Mad Badgers, Rosie confides her fears to a worried Al, and Luca tries to get Rob to open up. Malika finds herself inadvertently in a medical emergency and saves the life of a newborn.

episodes.name: Monstrous Regimen of Women
episodes.overview: There's an unexpected development when Bear encounters the police, and Scarlett and Ollies latest prank takes a wrong turn. Zara and Emma help a woman confront a residential home about how dangerous their 'care' for her mother is.

episodes.name: Starting Fires
episodes.overview: Jimmis patient Jay takes a chance on a new relationship, but things go from bad to worse.

episodes.name: Disorder
episodes.overview: Bear's date with Claudia doesnt go as well as planned. Nina tests Rosie and gets more than she bargained for. Meanwhile, Suni helps with a teenager who awakes after a violent incident with acute memory loss  but as his memory returns, it seems he was the perpetrator.

episodes.name: Father Figure
episodes.overview: Zara is flattered by Miles's flirting, and Rob finally addresses the elephant in the room and makes a huge decision. Al encounters a teenage boy who is convinced his sisters symptoms point to something supernatural.

episodes.name: Cold Call
episodes.overview: Bear is determined to fix things with Claudia, while Zara gets an unexpected message, and Al decides to cheer up Emma with a deliciously brilliant plan. When Scarlett is accused of theft, she starts to suspect that a fake carer is taking advantage of her elderly VPAS patients. She enlists Sunis help to uncover the truth.

episodes.name: Darker Dimensions
episodes.overview: Al is giddy with excitement and seeing double when he takes Emma to Mid Comic Con, but will Emma embrace the world of Darker Dimensions and its obsessive fans?

episodes.name: Rebirth
episodes.overview: Bear puts his foot in it with his receptionist team. Miles makes his move on Zara  but will she respond? Malika helps a labouring mother and her teenage daughter, struggling in very different ways with the impending new arrival.

episodes.name: The Forgotten Woman
episodes.overview: Its interview day, but which receptionist will win the role? Meanwhile, as Zara tries to lie low, Scarlett and Ollie up their game. Nancy hasnt been seen in months, but when Rob breaks into her flat, he makes a discovery that sends him on an important personal mission.

episodes.name: Blast from the Past
episodes.overview: Bear and Claudias fun day splinters, while Kirsty discovers Ninas plans for VPAS. Rosie tries her hand at diagnosing patients, much to Als chagrin.

episodes.name: Sore Point
episodes.overview: Zara tries to deal with Miles, while Daniel and Joe spend the day working together for a greener planet. Suni tries to help a friend and his new wife when they find out the hard way that not all secrets stay hidden.

episodes.name: Ladies and Gents
episodes.overview: Bear and Claudia go on a date, Zara is confronted by Professor Anwar over a photo, and Luca helps a woman who is being harassed about her gender.

episodes.name: Listen
episodes.overview: Rosie has her first day in charge as manager, Scarlett wonders why Rob moved out of Emma's, and Emma struggles with her decision to quit being an FME after a difficult case.

episodes.name: It Takes Two to Tango
episodes.overview: Scarlett has her first driving lesson, Jimmi tries to convince Emma to return to being an FME, Suni helps a dancing couple get back on their feet.

episodes.name: Sainted Sister
episodes.overview: Nina gives Rosie a task, Zara tries to deal with Miles, and Kirsty goes on her first VPAS visit and helps a broken family.

episodes.name: Bloodline, Part 1
episodes.overview: Nina helps at a charity fight night, which reveals secrets a family has tried to keep buried for years.

episodes.name: Bloodline, Part 2
episodes.overview: At the charity fight, the revelations of buried secrets threaten to tear a family apart.

episodes.name: Do Not Resuscitate
episodes.overview: Zara has some explaining to do, Emma and Al end up on the wrong side of Rosie, and on her first shift with Rob, Claudia is caught up in a family feud.

episodes.name: Kiss
episodes.overview: Daniel has a nasty surprise for Zara, and Claudia learns more about Bear. Meanwhile, Rosie tries to make amends.

episodes.name: Out in the Cold
episodes.overview: Al and Scarlett have to deal with a very angry patient, Ruhma has an unexpected encounter, and what next for Daniel and Zara?

episodes.name: Henry
episodes.overview: The Mill's staff try to deal with the shocking events of the previous night, Rosie has a surprising request for Barry, and Suni meets a young man trying to cope with the ghosts of his past.

episodes.name: Identity Crisis
episodes.overview: Bear tries to keep the peace when Frankie returns. Will Scarlett open up to Rob? And Jimmi is concerned about his latest counselling patient  but all is not what it seems...

episodes.name: Crime Never Pays?
episodes.overview: Can Zara get through to Daniel? Ruhma receives an unwanted reminder, and Sid has a run-in with a son determined to follow in his fathers criminal footsteps.

episodes.name: The Stolen Child
episodes.overview: Daniel and Zaras relationship teeters on the brink, while Bear and Claudias plans for a nice meal are foiled. Ruhma helps a desperate mother.

episodes.name: Put the Boot In
episodes.overview: Als great day turns south, while Daniel shields Joe from the truth. Bear fails to notice that Claudia is worried.

episodes.name: Alea Iacta Est
episodes.overview: Kirsty discovers something shocking, while Daniel has an encounter with the police. Bear is left confused by Claudias fractious behaviour.

episodes.name: Crashing
episodes.overview: Everyone at The Mill is on tenterhooks, while Joe spills the beans to Zara. Suni helps a patient after a drone crashes onto their roof.

episodes.name: The Bicycle Thief of Letherbridge
episodes.overview: The fallout from the Al situation continues at The Mill, while Bear surprises Claudia and gets more than he bargained for. Luca helps a courier when their bike gets stolen.

episodes.name: Exempt
episodes.overview: Scarlett tries to help an old school friend when shes assaulted outside The Mill.

episodes.name: One Over Par
episodes.overview: Daniels round of golf is ruined when a climate change protestor blockades the course. Emma becomes uncomfortable when Claudia asks her for advice. Daniel picks up Joe with dramatic consequences

episodes.name: Blue
episodes.overview: Zara is shocked by the news about Daniel and Joe. Jimmi tries to break down Als barriers but makes things worse.
